TOPICS COVERED (ENSEMBLE LEARNING & RANDOM FOREST)
Introduction to Ensemble Learning

The training session began with an introduction to Ensemble Learning, an advanced Machine Learning technique that combines multiple models to improve prediction accuracy, reliability, and overall performance. Learned that instead of relying on a single model, Ensemble Learning integrates the predictions of several models to produce a stronger and more robust final prediction.

The trainer explained that ensemble methods reduce prediction errors, improve model stability, and help overcome problems such as overfitting and underfitting. Discussed how Ensemble Learning is widely used in real-world AI applications due to its high predictive performance.

Why Ensemble Learning is Important

Studied the advantages of combining multiple Machine Learning models.

Learned that Ensemble Learning helps to:

Improve prediction accuracy.
Reduce variance and bias.
Increase model stability.
Handle complex datasets more effectively.
Improve generalization on unseen data.

Discussed how combining weak learners can produce a strong learner capable of achieving better results than individual models.

