Bagging (Bootstrap Aggregating)

Learned that Bagging creates multiple subsets of the training data using random sampling with replacement.

Studied the process:

Create several training datasets.
Train multiple models independently.
Combine predictions through majority voting (classification) or averaging (regression).

Discussed how Bagging reduces model variance and improves prediction stability.

