Introduction to Random Forest

Received a detailed introduction to Random Forest, one of the most popular Ensemble Learning algorithms.

Learned that Random Forest is an extension of Decision Trees that builds multiple decision trees and combines their predictions.

The trainer explained that Random Forest:

Creates multiple Decision Trees.
Uses random subsets of data and features.
Combines predictions using majority voting.

Discussed why Random Forest generally performs better than a single Decision Tree.

Working of Random Forest

Studied the complete workflow of Random Forest.

Learned the following steps:

Generate multiple bootstrap samples from the training dataset.
Build a separate Decision Tree for each sample.
Randomly select a subset of features at every split.
Train all trees independently.
Combine predictions using majority voting.

Understood how randomization improves diversity among trees and reduces overfitting.

