Advantages and Limitations of Random Forest

Discussed the strengths and limitations of the algorithm.

Advantages:

High prediction accuracy.
Reduces overfitting.
Handles large datasets efficiently.
Works with both classification and regression tasks.
Provides feature importance scores.
Robust to noisy data.

Limitations:

Higher computational cost.
Slower training compared to individual Decision Trees.
Less interpretable than a single Decision Tree.
Requires more memory for large forests.
